    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thurston</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your notes of the 15th and 26th ultimo; also of the 15th instant, all relating
                    to the alleged violation of the neutrality laws of the United States.</p>
                <p>In reply I have to say that copies of these notes were promptly transmitted to
                    the Attorney-General, that from you of the 15th instant having been communicated
                    to him yesterday.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
